<subSubSection id="4189652DFFE6692CFF236FC3D119AE91" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="092C36A6FFE6692CFF236FC3D119AE91" blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1295]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFF236FC3D406A995" bold="true" box="[199,315,909,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFEA56FC0D79EA995" authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Kozlov, 2019" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Kozlov" authorityYear="2019" box="[321,675,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brechlini" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFEA56FC0D48DA995" box="[321,432,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Lepturges</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFE246FC0D712A995" box="[448,559,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Lepturges</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFDDB6FC3D79EA995" box="[575,675,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">brechlini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="20D457CFFFE6692CFD4D6FC3D7C2A995" box="[681,767,909,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFC6A6FC0D1E8A995" authority="Monne, 1976" authorityName="Monne" authorityYear="1976" box="[910,1237,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC6A6FC0D698A995" box="[910,933,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC506FC0D6F6A995" box="[948,971,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC3E6FC3D104A995" box="[986,1081,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">funereus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6D024B57FFE6692CFBA46FC3D1E8A995" author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[1088,1237,909,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" pagination="43 - 98" refId="ref21196" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1976) Contribuic &quot; o ao conhecimento dos Acanthocinini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 30 (4), 43 - 98." type="journal article" year="1976">Monné, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="91A82A23FFE6692CFB076FC3D00BA995" box="[1251,1334,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–32. 22–25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1859,1884]" captionTargetBox="[220,1357,179,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[215,1361,179,1816]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–32. 22–25) Lepturges (Lepturges) brechlini, holotype male: 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Ventral habitus; 24) Lateral habitus; 25) Head, frontal view. 26) Lepturges (Lepturges) amabilis, dorsal habitus, syntype. 27) Lepturges (Lepturges) hahneli, dorsal habitus, holotype female. 28) Lepturges (Lepturges) funereus, dorsal habitus, holotype male. 29–32) Pseudosparna antonkozlovi, holotype male: 29) Head, frontal view; 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Ventral habitus; 32) Lateral habitus. Figures 26–28 by Jesus Santiago Moure (deceased)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2702269/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
), but differs by the elytral pubescence pattern, and by the posterolateral angles of the prothorax not spiniform. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFF326F98D72AA9DD" authority="Bates, 1863" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[214,535,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFF326F98D5D0A9DD" box="[214,237,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFF1B6F98D42BA9DD" box="[255,278,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFECC6F9BD4B5A9DD" box="[296,392,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">amabilis</emphasis>
Bates, 1863
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="91A82A23FFE6692CFDCC6F9BD746A9C2" box="[552,635,981,1008]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–32. 22–25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1859,1884]" captionTargetBox="[220,1357,179,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[215,1361,179,1816]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–32. 22–25) Lepturges (Lepturges) brechlini, holotype male: 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Ventral habitus; 24) Lateral habitus; 25) Head, frontal view. 26) Lepturges (Lepturges) amabilis, dorsal habitus, syntype. 27) Lepturges (Lepturges) hahneli, dorsal habitus, holotype female. 28) Lepturges (Lepturges) funereus, dorsal habitus, holotype male. 29–32) Pseudosparna antonkozlovi, holotype male: 29) Head, frontal view; 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Ventral habitus; 32) Lateral habitus. Figures 26–28 by Jesus Santiago Moure (deceased)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2702269/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) by the elytral pubescence pattern, and by the pale-yellowish color of this pubescence (grayish in 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFE2A6FB4D741AE21" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[462,636,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFE2A6FB4D4D8AE21" box="[462,485,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFE116FB4D731AE21" box="[501,524,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFDF86FB7D741AE21" box="[540,636,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">amabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFD706FB4D6CBAE21" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Kozlov" authorityYear="2019" box="[660,1014,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brechlini" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFD706FB4D63EAE21" box="[660,771,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Lepturges</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFCF76FB4D6BFAE21" box="[787,898,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Lepturges</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC766FB7D6CBAE21" box="[914,1014,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">brechlini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFB1E6FB4D407AE05" authority="Gilmour, 1959" authorityName="Gilmour" authorityYear="1959" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hahneli" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFB1E6FB4D02CAE21" box="[1274,1297,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFAC56FB4D005AE21" box="[1313,1336,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFAAC6FB7D0A1AE21" box="[1352,1436,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">hahneli</emphasis>
Gilmour, 1959
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="91A82A23FFE6692CFEAC6853D4A4AE05" box="[328,409,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–32. 22–25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1859,1884]" captionTargetBox="[220,1357,179,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[215,1361,179,1816]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–32. 22–25) Lepturges (Lepturges) brechlini, holotype male: 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Ventral habitus; 24) Lateral habitus; 25) Head, frontal view. 26) Lepturges (Lepturges) amabilis, dorsal habitus, syntype. 27) Lepturges (Lepturges) hahneli, dorsal habitus, holotype female. 28) Lepturges (Lepturges) funereus, dorsal habitus, holotype male. 29–32) Pseudosparna antonkozlovi, holotype male: 29) Head, frontal view; 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Ventral habitus; 32) Lateral habitus. Figures 26–28 by Jesus Santiago Moure (deceased)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2702269/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) by the elytral pubescence pattern, and shorter antennae (2.45 times elytral length in the new species, about 3 times elytral length in male of 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFD56680CD66AAE69" authorityName="Gilmour" authorityYear="1959" box="[690,855,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hahneli" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFD56680CD7F4AE69" box="[690,713,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFD3E680CD7CCAE69" box="[730,753,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFCE7680FD66AAE69" box="[771,855,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">hahneli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFC8B680CD1E9AE69" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Kozlov" authorityYear="2019" box="[879,1236,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brechlini" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC8B680CD6E3AE69" box="[879,990,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Lepturges</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC0B680CD163AE69" box="[1007,1118,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Lepturges</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFB94680FD1E9AE69" box="[1136,1236,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">brechlini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFAB0680CD4A6AE4D" authority="Bates, 1863" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perelegans" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFAB0680CD056AE69" box="[1364,1387,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFA98680CD0AEAE69" box="[1404,1427,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFF73682BD42CAE4D" box="[151,273,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">perelegans</emphasis>
Bates, 1863
</taxonomicName>
by the similar pattern of the elytral pubescence, but differs by the elytra slightly longer than 4 times the prothoracic length (slightly longer than 3 times in 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE6692CFCA868C4D129AE91" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[844,1044,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perelegans" subGenus="Lepturges">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFCA868C4D65EAE91" box="[844,867,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC9768C4D6B7AE91" box="[883,906,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFC7E68C7D129AE91" box="[922,1044,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">perelegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4189652DFFE6692CFF2368E3D75AAF3D" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="092C36A6FFE6692CFF2368E3D75AAF3D" blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1295]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE6692CFF2368E3D473AEF5" bold="true" box="[199,334,1197,1223]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to Ronald Brechlin (
<collectingCountry id="71847636FFE6692CFC6668E3D6CDAEF5" box="[898,1008,1197,1223]" name="Germany" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Germany</collectingCountry>
), saturniid and sphingid (Lepidoptera) specialist. Ronald has organized, financed and participated in numerous entomological expeditions in Central and South America over the last few decades.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
